# SalesVault – NestJS Backend Implementation Plan

Production-ready stock management backend for field sales teams. Based on the [README.md](file:///c:/Users/mrnad/OneDrive/Desktop/salesvault-stock-management%20system/README.md) spec.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **PostgreSQL must be running locally** (or you provide a connection string). The plan assumes `localhost:5432` with database `salesvault`. Please confirm your PostgreSQL setup.

> [!WARNING]
> **~60+ files** will be created inside `server-app/src/`. The existing scaffold files (`app.controller.ts`, `app.service.ts`) will be modified. The default `app.controller.spec.ts` will be updated.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Phase 1 — Project Foundation

#### [MODIFY] [package.json](file:///c:/Users/mrnad/OneDrive/Desktop/salesvault-stock-management%20system/server-app/package.json)
Install required dependencies:
```
Production: @nestjs/config, @nestjs/typeorm, typeorm, pg,
            @nestjs/jwt, @nestjs/passport, passport, passport-jwt,
            bcrypt, class-validator, class-transformer,
            helmet, @nestjs/throttler, uuid
Dev:        @types/bcrypt, @types/passport-jwt, @types/uuid
```

#### [NEW] [.env](file:///c:/Users/mrnad/OneDrive/Desktop/salesvault-stock-management%20system/server-app/.env)
```env
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_PORT=5432
DB_USERNAME=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=postgres
DB_NAME=salesvault
JWT_SECRET=<random-secret>
JWT_ACCESS_EXPIRY=15m
JWT_REFRESH_EXPIRY=7d
BCRYPT_ROUNDS=12
MAX_LOGIN_ATTEMPTS=5
LOCK_DURATION_MINUTES=30
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:8081
```

#### [MODIFY] [main.ts](file:///c:/Users/mrnad/OneDrive/Desktop/salesvault-stock-management%20system/server-app/src/main.ts)
- Add `helmet()`, CORS, `ValidationPipe` (whitelist + forbidNonWhitelisted), global exception filter
- Add API prefix `/api/v1`

