### Phase 3 — Database Entities

#### [NEW] `src/entities/` directory
| File | Key Columns |
|------|-------------|
| `user.entity.ts` | uuid PK, name, email (unique), password_hash, role, is_active, failed_attempts, locked_until, token_version, created_at, updated_at |
| `product.entity.ts` | uuid PK, name, sku (unique), price, cost_price, is_active, created_at |
| `warehouse.entity.ts` | uuid PK, name, location, created_at |
| `stock.entity.ts` | uuid PK, product_id FK, warehouse_id FK, quantity (CHECK >= 0), unique(product_id, warehouse_id) |
| `stock-assignment.entity.ts` | uuid PK, salesperson_id FK, product_id FK, warehouse_id FK, quantity_assigned, quantity_remaining (CHECK >= 0), assigned_at |
| `sale.entity.ts` | uuid PK, salesperson_id FK, total_amount, payment_status, idempotency_key (unique), notes, created_at |
| `sale-item.entity.ts` | uuid PK, sale_id FK, product_id FK, quantity, unit_price, line_total |
| `activity-log.entity.ts` | uuid PK, user_id FK, action_type, entity_type, entity_id, old_data (jsonb), new_data (jsonb), ip_address, device_info, previous_hash, current_hash, created_at |
| `refresh-token.entity.ts` | uuid PK, user_id FK, token_hash, device_info, ip_address, expires_at, is_revoked, created_at |

---

### Phase 4 — Auth Module

#### [NEW] `src/auth/` directory
| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `auth.module.ts` | Module registration (JwtModule, PassportModule) |
| `auth.controller.ts` | `POST /auth/login`, `POST /auth/refresh`, `POST /auth/logout` |
| `auth.service.ts` | Login validation, token generation, refresh rotation, account locking |
| `strategies/jwt.strategy.ts` | Passport JWT strategy (validates token, checks user active + token version) |
| `dto/login.dto.ts` | email, password validation |
| `dto/refresh-token.dto.ts` | refresh_token validation |
| `dto/auth-response.dto.ts` | Response shape |

**Security features:**
- bcrypt password hashing (12 rounds)
- Account lock after 5 failed attempts, unlock after 30 min
- JWT access token (15 min) + refresh token (7 days)
- Refresh token rotation (old token revoked on use)
- Token version on user → force logout all sessions
- Session/device tracking via refresh_token table

