## Verification Plan

### Automated — Build Check
```bash
cd server-app
npm run build
```
Must compile with **zero errors**.

### Automated — Existing Tests
```bash
cd server-app
npm run test
```
The existing `app.controller.spec.ts` test will be updated to match the new health-check endpoint. Tests should pass.

### Manual Verification
1. **Ensure PostgreSQL is running** with database `salesvault` created
2. Run `npm run start:dev` — server should start on port 3000
3. Hit `GET http://localhost:3000/api/v1/` → should return `{ status: 'ok' }`
4. Check console output for TypeORM connection success
5. Verify tables are created in PostgreSQL via `psql` or any DB client

> [!NOTE]
> Full API endpoint testing (login, CRUD, sales transactions) will require a running PostgreSQL instance. If you don't have one, you can use Docker: `docker run --name salesvault-pg -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres -e POSTGRES_DB=salesvault -p 5432:5432 -d postgres:16`
